##### From the seaborn, we can directly see the trends and patterns that indicate a statistical relationship between each variable. 

##### In the Gender variable, it is a hugely difference performance between male and female when they in the task. Males is more likely off-task than females when we consider the grade, total time, and totalobs-forsession variables. Thus, male possibly will have off-task issue when they get higher grade level, longer time when they join in activity, and more observations made per session. In addition, Malesâ€™ performance worse than female in NumACTIVITY, TRANSITIONS, NumFORMATS , FORMATchanges , and Obsv/act. From the seaborn chart, male might concentrate at the first, but they will be off task when the transitions or the formats of activity gradually increase the number of times. 

##### In the activity variable, Acitivy_Dancing is the activity that have the greatest number of off-tasks compared to other activity. The Activity_individual seems like the second activity showing the data of off-tasks. Activity_Wholecarpet and Activity_Wholedesks are both likely showing the data of off-tasks. Activity_Smallgroup and Activity_testing are showing the more data of on-tasks.

# accurancy score
from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score
ac_logit1 = accuracy_score(ONTASK_logit, ONTASK_pred_logit1)

print("The accuracy for logistic regression in sklearn is", ac_logit1*100, "%")

##### We used the logistic regression to build the classifier with the training dataset. 

##### The coefficients of variables indicate that when we control all other variables, to what extent the individual variable could impact the result of the model. We could see the different impacts that each variable brings to the model by looking at the sign of their coefficients. According to the results, the variables, including Activity_Dancing, Activity_Smallgroup, Activity_Testing, NumACTIVITIES, TRANSITIONS, NumFORMATS, and Obsv/act, will increase the likelihood of ONTASK because their coefficients are positive. In particular, Activity_Testing has the greatest influence on model result. It is reasonable that students are more concentrated when they are taking a test. On the other hand, the variables, including GRADE, Activity_Individual, Total Time, Transitions/Durations, FORMATchanges, Activity_Wholecarpet, and Activity_Wholedesks, will negatively impact the result of the model due to their negative coefficients. Activity_Wholedesks will decrease the likelihood of ONTASK because it has the smallest negative coefficient. When a few students are involved in one task, they are likely to be distracted or do not have to dedicate on the work.

##### Then we compared the Ys predicted by the model with data in validation dataset, the accurancy for logistic regression is about 66.67%.
